This paper is about improving the state-of-the-art end-to-end neural coreference model, which is a natural language processing task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses deep learning techniques, which suggests it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions using a biaffine attention model, which is a technique commonly used in computer vision, suggesting it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper mentions optimizing the model's performance, which could suggest it belongs to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
